I"ã<blockquote>
  <p>Better than using quotes and plus symbol each time, which produces a new string every time a plus symbol is used.</p>
</blockquote>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>
    int nephew1Age = 9;
    int nephew2Age = 12;
    int nephew3Age = 14;

    System.out.printf("The ages of my nephew's are %d, %d, %d%n", nephew1Age, nephew2Age, nephew3Age);
</code></pre></div></div>

